        <h2>About the work</h2>
        <p>The novel "Eugene Onegin" was written by Alexander Sergeyevich Pushkin in 1823-1831. Russian Russian literature The work is one of the most significant creations of Russian literature, according to Belinsky, it is the "encyclopedia of Russian life" of the early nineteenth century.</p>
        <p>The novel in Pushkin's poems "Eugene Onegin" belongs to the literary direction of realism, although in the first chapters the influence of Romanticism traditions on the author is still noticeable. There are two storylines in the work: the central one is the tragic love story of Eugene Onegin and Tatiana Larina, and the secondary one is the friendship of Onegin and Lensky.</p>
