        <p>The place of action is the estates of Onegin, Larin, St. Petersburg.</p>
        <p>The novel covers the events from 1819 to 1825: from the foreign campaigns of the Russian army after the defeat of Napoleon to the Decembrist uprising. These were the years of development of Russian society, the reign of Alexander I. In general, the novel Eugene Onegin reflected the events of the first quarter of the XIX century, that is, the time of creation and the time of action of the novel roughly coincide.
